(73, 'Attendees: Full Z47 team: Briskpe Views RC -Weak Maybe Archetype 3/4 +Liked Indu a little more than Aloke and Sanjay, FMF- Below 5 + More than expected amount of work on regulatory piece and customers. + Ahead in terms of reg thinking and execution compared to others. ? Bold choice on the segment → Feels like they’ve underestimated the challenges of the segment they are going after though. Not sure they’re fully cognizant of digital strengths of the other players / are thinking along those lines. Avi – Very easy pass Low Archetype, IFs + Aloke has some conviction. ? FMF is 0, Not my archetype → Indu is just words not content - Struggling to give a clincher reason why to pass , “there’s a few things such as the teams background that makes you pause they say some of the right things but it never really ties together.” ?Complete IFs stumbling from one insight to another. ? Not sure if the refs on Sanjay are high quality. (Would not give any weight to Gaurav Chopra’s ref either) → Navin might have a positive view but he likes these kind of founding team. ? Sanjay is someone who has never compounded in life, and everything he has done post HDFC (Venture Studio) is scattered → This journey also seems scattered. VV-Weak maybe Insight / spike missing / edge missing. Depth in biz model / product etc Sanjay more thoughtful than I gave him credit for Team, Talent, Cost/frugality, pivot at the right time, bend at the right time 7 days digital journey vs offline; more digital thinking tha...'),
(75, 'RM notes: Next steps - BRC w/ DoWhile AI CoFo from RM + 2PE with Kinzy & Bunny with RA & Mohit Notes 1. Naman Jain - Elder brother 1. Nishchal Jain - Younger brother 1. Startup journey 1. DoWhile AI 1. Tinkering together post SPC and LossFunk 1. Buny 1. Why pendant? 1. Started to spend too much time on hardware - “juice is in AI” 1. How did walkie talkie come about? 1. Demo video 1. Cash Q: Why not go full fictional characters like EMoMee? 1. Cash Q: Hardware - why not make it a analogue kid mobile? 1. What are you hiring for? 1. Parent mobile 1. Initial market (?) 1. Comps: 1. Can offer personalized learning storybooks | learning activities → personalized 1. Customers 1. Learning from Osmo founder - keep founder healthy & high 1. $150 retail price for hardware 1. Technology
RM Notes: 1. Shubham knows Deepak 1. Knows Aniket Kamte from Nexus VP 1. Left Google because he wanted to take some risk 1. Joined DoWhile AI when it was called Collective AI 1. v/s othr companies 1. Mandalin is his current co 1. Convinction / motivation lacking at the firm - didn’t have as many wins 1. Going to meet them in SF 1. Come a long way - motivated now versus before 1. He feels choice of market isn’t something he would do 1. They need a CTO/ VPEng
Cash reflections -  Weak Maybe. Community cheque at best.: 1. Pure inside out FFs with no clear consumer spike 1. Have built and landed on a much better form factor (hardware and software) in the entire audio ai toy for kids than all other teams we hav...'),
(78, 'RM reflections - dead center Maybe | 0.5% cheque = $150K IFF we go ahead w/ this: ++ Pedigreed team given 4 YOE @ Loom - worked closely w/ founders on the Loom AI launch ++ Thesis (MUCH more than Cash & KB): For me, this it Limitless 1.0 i.e. agent running in the background learning everything about you ++ Design principle struck a deep chord with me: Voice to be used for editing the “first draft” created by the Caddy Agent ++ Good set of learnings captured by them - Enterprise plan beyond billing consolidation & SSO ++ Do sense they have GTM chops; not just Product builders - but yet to be proven out / demonstrated ?? Worried that they will repeat the same Loom mistakes i.e. build a horizontal OS level product which will struggle to capture Enterprise revenue ?? Worried that their landing wedge is dictation - didn’t hear anything about actions - therefore, Wispr Flow is the competition ?? Underestimating the amount of configuration & customization needed to make even dictation work Mid Feb ‘26 launch Key Qs - business 1. Why choose to go after this problem? 1. Why standalone app & not OS level solution? 1. What do “actions” require v/s Wispr which is transcribing today
RM’s suggestion = 0.5% ownership i.e. $150K cheque 2025-12-12T22:39:00.000+05:30: BRC w/ Joe (Loom CoFo) took me from Maybe to SM - sticking to the 0.5% ownership target i.e. $150K cheque size Why $150K? - Connor (founder we are underwriting) is Spiky = 1 - rapid career trajectory from intern to Eng to PM to G...')
