(88, 'Discussion on 20.09.2024: 1. Cash flow position 1. Learnings so far 1. Business right now 1. Discussions with others 1. Next steps 1. RM Reflections
Investor updates (since RM is an Angel): [Page: April 2024 Update] [Page: May 2024 update] [Page: June 2024 update] [Page: July 2024 update] [Page: August 2024 update]'),
(90, 'Z47 meeting 2025-10-23: KK Overall view: WM for DeVC Spikey: 0 to 0.5 ++ resourseful ++ hustler ++ intellectually honest ++ outside in ++ staying right things on thesis ?? numerate not much ?? not commercial ?? no consumer insight TK Overall View: WM to Maybe- for DeVC and WM for Z Spikey: 0 Spike Needed: consumer/product and exec ops ++ hustler and hardworking ++ highly iterative; take  customer feedback and improve ++ Jugaadu types; copy insight from other companies and them execute ++ Dhandha mindset ?? Not brand builder types ?? still have more drop shipping mentality; look at trends and some learnings from Kishore biyani; quickly copy it without thinking much ?? no unique thought process ?? trying to too do many things at the same time ?? no key differentiation Detailed Meeting Notes (23.10.25) Founder Background - Vedang (22), Psychology major; started Clapstore in 2020 during COVID lockdown while in 11th–12th grade - First-time founder from a family of educators (mother: govt college lecturer, father: tuition teacher); driven by desire to be first in family to build a business and have autonomy - Initially aspired to join defense services; COVID shifted focus to entrepreneurship—started with dropshipping via TikTok (US market), scaled to ₹6–7L per month before facing supplier scams - Transitioned from dropshipping to buying from manufacturers and managing own packaging/dispatch; later evolved into designing and manufacturing products after discovering success with non-...'),
(92, 'Ref from Anand (CEO @ MinIO): Got a ref from Anand, CEO @ MinIO; Great kid and sharp, but concerns on 0-1 and will leave this in the pass category for us. - Top 3 engineers for his tenure that AB has seen over the years - Problem solver and will be able to figure out any domain you through at him - Steep learnings curve - Humble, seeks advice, etc - H&H - worked amongst the hardest in his team ? Needs direction for 0-1. someone has to guide him the right direction. Can solve problems, but needs a guiding hand on what problem to focus on; ? Not angel investing because of the domain. AB doesnt get the space and not sure why sid picked it. Detailed notes Anand context - deeply involved in product and engineering side - he was part of our AI team - he was under 2 other AI leads - He started as an intern - he was a fresher but worked at a senior engineer levl - he was part of senior discussions as well - very good problem sovler - he is the perfect kid every parents dreams of - very skilled, hardowrking, no bad habits, sharp - He works really hard; hardest in the team - Skillset wise - fast learner - very sharp learning curve - how you think about rpoblem solving and picking the right approach, he had good clarity - what i dont know enough - his domain in real estate - picked real estate as a market but i cant guage enough on wether its a real problem - realtors are bad customers - dont know how big it is - Relative grading to others - dont like interns - but he was one of the few...'),
(94, 'Ashwin''s Series A Notes - Summary - 2026-01-30: **Founders:** Akash, Neel, Prajwal - All IITM ''22 grads, no prior work experience. **Round:** Series A - $10M raise, wants $80M post. Has offer from US fund at lower valuation. **KP Views:** WMB and pass - also speaking to seed investor for reference. **NOTE FOR V:** FYI in case you''d like to meet them, but Ashwin doesn''t see us doing this round. --- **POSITIVES** **Tech spike:** Strong technical team solving tough challenges. **Founder quality:** "Akash is sharp and spiky on intrinsics. Not overly aggressive, but he''s consistently been at it." **Traction (~$2M ARR):** Added ~$1M ARR in last 6 months. --- **CONCERNS** **Thesis - AI-first Loom:** Shoot explainer/product videos with AI voiceovers, graphics, auto-zoom. "Started with L&D, then moved to sales, then customer success, and now thinking of jumping to marketing. Overall, the approach feels too iterative for my liking - throwing 10 things at a wall to see what sticks." **GTM:** "Growth is good, but there''s still no repeatable GTM motion. It feels sporadic and heavily LinkedIn-driven (founder posts)." **ACVs:** Mostly less than $5K. Largest enterprise customer ~$40K, but most are small teams. **Auto content updating:** Looking to launch feature connecting to video repositories. "Companies like GitHub have dedicated teams for this, so it could be an interesting thesis. But given how much they''ve jumped around historically, I''m not confident this will stick either."'),
(95, 'Marketscan & Breakdown by Trinika 2025-09-12: Hi Team, Adding the breakdown of market landscape and workflow in the excel here Quick summary of key questions below: ![](cid:3199483326*image001.png@01DC22BC.55A4C510) Is the problem big enough? - Yes, because in a content/video production process, three prep tasks - proxy creation, renaming/restructuring, and audio–video sync - together take ~5-7% of the total production budget and ~10-15% of assistant editor time. - Example: a 60-second ad or micro-drama with 4 cameras and separate sound typically needs 20-30hrs from AE before the first cut - iteration speed is higher for microdrama so faster speed req - TAM (for these three steps): Global ~$3B; US ~$1.2B. - SAM (automation wedge): Global ~$1.5B; US ~$0.5B. - At 10% penetration of SAM: ~$150M ARR global; ~$50M ARR US Big gaps in workflow today? - Camera card to storage: For most cameras, copying from card to local drive and cloud is still manual. Only Canon paired with Frame.io (Adobe-owned) auto-copies to both. - Transfer & naming: Cameras save files as C0001 or A002C012; editors need script-friendly names like Scene3_Take5. Renaming remains manual. - Project & bins: Folders nomenclature varies from agencies to agencies – some do it by - day, by actor, or scene. No tool auto-restructures into clean bins/folder by scene/shot/take. - Audio–video sync: Tools handle clear lip-sync, but struggle when lips aren’t visible or timing is creative. Example: a voice-over on a montage, or...')
ON CONFLICT (company_id) DO UPDATE SET content = EXCLUDED.content;

